ence</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Building_age-appropriate_confidence_in_the_early_years_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1691664405" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Building_age-appropriate_confidence_in_the_early_years_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1691664405 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Building_age-appropriate_confidence_in_the_early_years_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1691664405 320w" width="1330" height="900" alt="Building age-appropriate confidence in the early years - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Building age-appropriate confidence in the early years - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-31_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-32_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-34_">The early years of a child's life are the foundation for their future self-esteem and confidence. Module 1 of the training course focuses on strategies to cultivate age and stage-appropriate confidence in young minds. This involves creating an environment that encourages exploration, experimentation, and mastery of new skills.<br><br>By allowing children to engage in age-appropriate challenges, educators and caregivers can foster a sense of accomplishment, enabling them to believe in their abilities.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-35_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-37_">Nurturing the 'Can Do' child</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Nurturing_the_Can_Do_child_-_Building_confidence_in_the_early_years_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1691664482" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Nurturing_the_Can_Do_child_-_Building_confidence_in_the_early_years_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1691664482 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Nurturing_the_Can_Do_child_-_Building_confidence_in_the_early_years_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1691664482 320w" width="1944" height="1298" alt="Nurturing the ‘Can Do’ child - Building confidence in the early years - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Nurturing the ‘Can Do’ child - Building confidence in the early years - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-38_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-39_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-41_">A 'Can Do' attitude is a powerful asset that significantly influences a child's development. Module 2 of the training course offers valuable insights into promoting and supporting the growth of a 'Can Do' child. This entails creating a supportive atmosphere where children are encouraged to take initiative, solve problems, and face setbacks with determination.<br><br>By recognising and celebrating small achievements, adults play a pivotal role in nurturing a mindset that believes in possibilities and resilience.<br> </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-42_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-44_">Empowering practitioners, parents, and adults</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Empowering_practitioners_parents_and_adults_-_Building_resilience_and_confidence_in_the_early_years_training_programme_-_The_Mandatory_Traini.png?v=1691664529" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Empowering_practitioners_parents_and_adults_-_Building_resilience_and_confidence_in_the_early_years_training_programme_-_The_Mandatory_Traini.png?v=1691664529 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Empowering_practitioners_parents_and_adults_-_Building_resilience_and_confidence_in_the_early_years_training_programme_-_The_Mandatory_Traini_500x.png?v=1691664529 320w" width="1455" height="970" alt="Empowering practitioners, 